  "name": "Underdark Scout",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/perception/shadow-stealth-eyes-purple.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 3rd level, you master the art of the ambush. You have advantage on initiative rolls and have the following benefits during your first turn in combat:</p><ul><li><p>You gain a +10 bonus to your movement speed.</p></li><li><p>If you use the Attack action, you can make one additional attack.</p></li><li><p>You have <strong>advantage</strong> on attack rolls against creatures that have not yet acted in initiative.</p></li></ul><p>You are also adept at evading creatures that rely on <strong>darkvision</strong>. Such creatures gain no benefit when attempting to detect you in dark and dim conditions. Additionally, when the DM determines if you can hide from a creature, that creature gains no benefit from its darkvision.</p>",
